#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""nvmoe — run flagship MoE models from your NVMe on a small GPU.

    ./nvmoe doctor                     is this machine ready?
    ./nvmoe list                       verified models + what's local
    ./nvmoe run qwen3-30b-2507         download -> repack -> verify -> serve
    ./nvmoe run qwen3-30b-2507 --port 8901 --ctx 32768
    ./nvmoe plan qwen3-30b-2507        what to expect on this hardware
    ./nvmoe stop                       stop the server this tool started

`run` is idempotent: every stage is skipped if its output already exists
(the download resumes if interrupted). The server it starts is plain
`llama-server` — an OpenAI-compatible endpoint; point any chat UI at
http://localhost:<port>/v1. Python 3.10+ stdlib only, like the rest of
the repo.
"""

